The paper deals with channel estimation and interference mitigation in cognitive radio networks, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of beamforming and multiple antennas also suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes the use of minimum mean square error (MMSE) framework, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
